ragon|Agnes of Aquitaine I]]<br>after 1049<br>no children\n|| Natural son of Sancho III, received Aragon.\n|-bgcolor=#dac \n|| [[Gonzalo of Sobrarbe and Ribagorza|Gonzalo S\u00e1nchez II]]\n||\n||1020\n||1035-1045\n||26 June 1045\n||[[County of Sobrarbe|Sobrarbe]] & [[County of Ribagorza|Ribagorza]] \n||''Unmarried''\n|| Son of Sancho III, received the counties of Sobrarbe and Ribagorza, which came from his mother, who had rights over those territories. Left no descendants, and his territories went to his half-brother Ramiro.\n|-bgcolor=#dac \n|colspan=\"8\" align=\"center\"|''Sobrabe and Ribagorza were absorbed by Aragon''\n|-bgcolor=#acd \n|| [[Garc\u00eda S\u00e1nchez III of Pamplona|Garcia IV (S\u00e1nchez III) ''of N\u00e1jera'']]\n|| [[File:Garcia Sanchez III.jpg|100px]]\n||1012\n||1035-1054\n||1 September 1054\n||[[Kingdom of Navarre|Pamplona]]\n||[[Stephanie, Queen of Navarre|Stephanie of Foix]]<br>1038<br>[[Barcelona]]<br>eight children\n|| Son of Sancho III, received Pamplona.\n|-bgcolor=#dcb \n|| '''[[Ferdinand I of Le\u00f3n|Ferdinand I ''the Great'']]'''\n|| [[File:Fernando I, rey de Castilla y Le\u00f3n (Museo del Prado).jpg|100px]]\n||1016\n||1029-1037<br><br>1037-1065<br>'''(1056)'''\n||27 December 1065\n||[[County of Castile|Castile]]<br><br>[[County of Castile|Castile]] & [[Kingdom of Le\u00f3n|Le\u00f3n]]\n||[[Sancha of Le\u00f3n|Sancha, Queen of Le\u00f3n]]<br>1032<br>five children\n|| Son of Sancho III, received the county of Castile from his mother, Muniadona, in 1029. He also ruled, ''jure uxoris'', the [[Kingdom of Le\u00f3n]] with his wife Sancha from 1037.\n|-bgcolor=#acd \n|| [[Sancho IV of Pamplona|Sancho IV ''the Noble'']] \n|| [[File:Sancho IV the Noble.jpg|100px]]\n||1039\n||1054-1076\n||4 June 1076\n||[[Kingdom of Navarre|Pamplona]]\n||[[Plaisance of Normandy]]<br>c.1068<br>three children\n|| Assassinated. He left a minor child, Garcia Sanchez, but he was considered not fit for the throne for his age, and the throne was given to the king of Aragon.\n|-bgcolor=#bac \n|| [[Sancho Ram\u00edrez|Sancho I & V]]\n|| [[File:Sancho Rem\u00edriz.jpg|100px]]\n||1042\n||1063-1076<br><br>1076-1094\n||4 June 1094\n||[[Kingdom of Aragon|Aragon]]<br><br>[[Kingdom of Aragon|Aragon]] & [[Kingdom of Pamplona|Pamplona]]\n||[[Isabella of Urgell]]<br>1065<br>''(annulled 1070)''<br>one child<br><br>[[Felicia of Roucy]]<br>1076<br>three children\n|| Son of Ramiro I, was chosen as the new king of Pamplona in 1076, reuniting both kingdoms once more.\n|-bgcolor=#dcb \n|| [[Sancho II of Castile|Sancho II ''the Strong'']]\n|| [[File:Sancho II de Castilla (Museo del Prado).jpg|100px]]\n||1038/9\n||1065-1071<br><br>1071-1072\n||7 October 1072\n||[[Kingdom of Castile|Castile]]<br><br>[[Kingdom of Castile|Castile]] & [[Kingdom of Le\u00f3n|Le\u00f3n]]\n||Alberta<br>no children\n|| Son of Ferdinand I, from 1071 deposed his brothers and took briefly control of all the inheritance of his father, before he was assassinated.\n|-bgcolor=#dcb\n|colspan=8 align=\"center\"|''Castile was reabsorbed in Le\u00f3n''\n|-bgcolor=#deb \n|| [[Garcia II of Galicia|Garcia II]]\n|| [[File:Garcia II of Galicia.jpg|100px]]\n||1042\n||1065-1071\n||21 March 1090\n||[[Kingdom of Galicia|Galicia]]\n||''Unmarried''\n|| Son of Ferdinand I, from 1071 he was deposed by Sancho II; tried to return after Sancho's assassination, but Alfonso arrested and banished him to the Castle of Luna, where he eventually died many years later.\n|-bgcolor=#deb \n|colspan=8 align=\"center\"|''Galicia was reabsorbed in Castile, and then in Le\u00f3n''\n|-bgcolor=#bca\n|| '''[[Alfonso VI of Le\u00f3n|Alfonso VI ''the Brave'']]'''\n|| [[File:El rey Alfonso VI de Le\u00f3n (Museo del Prado).jpg|100px]]\n||1040\n||1065-1071 <br><br> 1072-1109<br>'''(1077)'''\n||21 March 1090\n||[[Kingdom of Le\u00f3n|Le\u00f3n]]<br><br>[[Kingdom of Le\u00f3n|Le\u00f3n]] & [[Kingdom of Castile|Castile]]\n||[[Agnes of Aquitaine, Queen of Le\u00f3n and Castile|Agnes of Aquitaine II]]<br>1073/4<br>no 