ign=\"center\"|''With the death of Urraca the line of the Jimena family died out in Le\u00f3n & Castile, which were inherited by [[Alfonso VII of Le\u00f3n and Castile]], from the [[House of Ivrea]]''.\n|-bgcolor=#acd \n|| [[Garc\u00eda Ram\u00edrez of Navarre|Garcia V (Ram\u00edrez) ''the Restorer'']]\n|| [[File:King of Navarre GarciaIV-ret.jpg|100px]]\n||?\n||1134-1150\n||21 November 1150\n||[[Kingdom of Navarre|Pamplona]]\n||[[Margaret of L'Aigle]]<br>1130<br>four children<br><br>[[Urraca of Castile, Queen of Navarre|Urraca of Castile ''the Asturian'']]<br>24 June 1144<br>[[Le\u00f3n (historical region)|Le\u00f3n]]<br>no children\n|| Grandson of Sancho Garc\u00e9s, illegitimate son of [[Garc\u00eda S\u00e1nchez III of Pamplona|Garcia IV (S\u00e1nchez III) of Pamplona]].\n|-bgcolor=#bac \n|| [[Ramiro II of Aragon|Ramiro II ''the Monk'']]\n|| [[File:Remiro II d'Arag\u00f3n.jpg|100px]]\n||24 April 1086\n||1134-1157\n||16 August 1157\n||[[Kingdom of Aragon|Aragon]] \n||[[Agnes of Aquitaine, Queen of Aragon|Agnes of Aquitaine IV]]<br>13 November 1135<br>[[Jaca]]<br>''(annulled 1136/7)''<br>one child\n|| Last surviving son of Sancho I/V. Withdrawn fom monastic life to inherit the throne.\n|-bgcolor=#acd \n|| [[Sancho VI of Navarre|Sancho VI ''the Wise'']]\n|| [[File:SanchoelSabio.jpg|100px]]\n||1133\n||1150-1194\n||27 June 1194\n||[[Kingdom of Navarre|Navarre]]\n||[[Sancha of Castile, Queen of Navarre|Sancha of Castile]]<br>2 June 1157<br>[[Carri\u00f3n de los Condes]]<br>six children\n|| He was the first monarch to adopt the title ''King of Navarre''.\n|-bgcolor=#bac \n|| [[Petronilla of Aragon|Petronilla I]]\n|| [[File:Peronella-Ramires-reina-d'Arag\u00f3.jpg|100px]]\n||29 June/11 August 1136\n||1157-1164\n||15 October 1173\n||[[Kingdom of Aragon|Aragon]] \n||[[Ramon Berenguer IV, Count of Barcelona]]<br>August 1150<br>[[Lleida]]<br>five children\n|| Only daughter of Ramiro II, abdicated in 1164 to his son, to pursue a monastic life for herself.\n|-bgcolor=#bac\n|colspan=8 align=\"center\"|''With the death of Petronilla the line of the Jimena family died out in Aragon, which was inherited by [[Alfonso II of Aragon]], from the [[House of Barcelona]]''.\n|-bgcolor=#acd \n|| [[Sancho VII of Navarre|Sancho VII ''the Strong'']]\n|| [[File:Sancho VII the Strong.jpg|100px]]\n||17 April 1154\n||1194-1234\n||7 April 1234\n||[[Kingdom of Navarre|Navarre]]\n||[[Constance of Toulouse]]<br>1195<br>''(annulled 1200)''<br>no children\n|| Left no descendants. The Navarrese throne went to his french nephew, the count of Champagne.\n|-bgcolor=#acd \n|colspan=8 align=\"center\"|''With the death of Sancho VII the line of the Jimena family died out in Navarre, which were inherited by [[Theobald I of Navarre]], from the [[House of Champagne]]. As Sancho VII was the last living member of the family at the time of his death, Jimena dynasty became extinct after his death.''\n|}\n\n==Family tree of the House of Jim\u00e9nez==\n{{familytree/start}}\n{{familytree | | | | | | | | | Az1 | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | Ini |Az1=[[Aznar Gal\u00edndez I|Aznar I]]<br>count of Aragon<br>HOUSE OF COUNTS OF ARAGON|Ini=[[\u00cd\u00f1igo Arista of Pamplona|\u00cd\u00f1igo]]<br>king of Pamplona<br>HOUSE OF \u00cd\u00d1IGUEZ}}\n{{familytree | | | | | | | | | |!| | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | |!}}\n{{familytree | | | | | | | | | Gal | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | Gar |Gal=[[Galindo Azn\u00e1rez I|Galindo I]]<br>count of Aragon|Gar=[[Garc\u00eda \u00cd\u00f1iguez of Pamplona|Garc\u00eda]]<br>king of Pamplona}}\n{{familytree | | | | | | | | | |)|-|-|-|-|-|-|-|-|-|-|-|-|-|-|-|.| | | |!}}\n{{familytree | | | | | | | | | |!| | | |,|-|-|-|-|-|-|-|-|-|-|-|*|-|-|-|+|-|-|-|.}}\n{{familytree | | | | | | | | | Az2 |~| One | | Jim | | | | | | dau |~| Sao | | For |dau=(daughter)|Az2=[[Aznar Gal\u00edndez II|Athnar II]]<br>count of Aragon|One=Onneca Garc\u00e9s|Jim=Jim\u00e9no<br>'''HOUSE OF JIM\u00c9NES'''|Sao=Sancho|For=[[Fort\u00fan Garc\u00e9s of Pamplona|Fort\u00